<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="vote-v">vote <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /vəʊt/    美 /voʊt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>投票；表决：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Black people could not vote or choose their leaders.
黑人不能参加选举，也不能选择自己的领导人。</p><footer>人教① – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>TV viewers <strong>vote for</strong> their favorite person on the show.
节目过程中，电视观众可以给他们最喜欢的选手投票。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>投票评选</strong></h4>
<p>to choose sb for a particular position or prize：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Six of Zindel’s books have been voted the Best Books for Young Adults.
金代尔有6本书已被选为“最佳青少年读物”。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>voter /'vəʊtə(r)/ n [C]  </p></div>